Analyzing simulated cyberattacks within a controlled SOC laboratory environment, including brute force attacks, phishing simulations.

The investigation involved:

Documenting attack timelines from initial access attempt to detection
Identifying Indicators of Compromise (IOCs) from Apache logs and Splunk SIEM data
Mapping observed attacker behaviour to the MITRE ATT&CK framework
Assessing impact and potential risks of each simulated attack
Developing appropriate remediation and containment strategies
MITRE ATT&CK Mapping

Observed behaviours were mapped to MITRE ATT&CK techniques:

T1110 – Brute Force (Hydra attacks)
T1078 – Valid Accounts (SSH authentication attempts)
T1190 – Exploit Public-Facing Application (DVWA exploitation)
